Decides whether a previously saved checkpoint is still safe to resume.
Evaluates sync.checkpoint.resume-safe via the Rule Engine when available;
falls back to the resume-window hours from .

Fluent builder that describes which default values should be applied to the
fields of a named entity (entityName) when a new record is created.



var profile = EntityDefaultsProfile.For("Users")
    .Set("CreatedBy",  ":USERNAME")   // expression — resolved at runtime
    .Set("CreatedAt",  ":NOW")         // expression
    .Set("Id",         ":NEWGUID")     // expression
    .Set("Status",     "Active")       // literal — used as-is
    .Set("Version",    "1");           // literal

DefaultsManager.RegisterProfile("mydb", profile);
DefaultsManager.Apply(editor, "mydb", "Users", record);

Discovers, caches, and auto-registers third-party 
plugins that are decorated with .

Uses IDMEEditor.assemblyHandler.ConfigEditor.DefaultResolverClasses for
discovery — the same mechanism as [AddinAttribute] connectors,
[PipelinePluginAttribute] ETL plugins, and [FileReaderAttribute]
file-format readers.

Calling  also calls 
for each found resolver so that all existing code that uses
DefaultsManager.Apply(…) picks up the plugin automatically.

Typical usage:

  // After assemblyHandler has loaded all plugins:
  var registry = new DefaultResolverRegistry(editor);
  registry.Discover();   // finds all [DefaultResolver(…)]-attributed classes

  // Look up a descriptor:
  if (registry.TryGet("TenantContextResolver", out var desc))
      Console.WriteLine(desc.Attribute.SupportedTokens);

